---
/**
 * ai-evaluation/0001 · Figure 1 — "The eval loop in one frame" (hero).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/ai-evaluation/lessons/0001-evaluation-fundamentals-offline-online.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup>). It lives as an .astro
 * component, NOT inline in the MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with
 * raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size,
 * stroke-width, marker-end, …) and self-referential ids.
 *
 * The source page defines four shared arrowhead <marker>s (#arw, #arwG, #arwR,
 * #arwM) once in a hidden global <svg> in <body>; every figure on the page
 * references them via marker-end="url(#…)". That hidden defs block is reproduced
 * here, in the FIRST figure on the page, so the markers resolve document-wide
 * for Figs 1–5 (ids are kept as-is to match the source DOM and the #s1 anchors).
 */
---

<svg width="0" height="0" style="position:absolute" aria-hidden="true"
    ><defs>
        <marker
            id="arw"
            viewBox="0 0 10 10"
            refX="8.5"
            refY="5"
            markerWidth="7"
            markerHeight="7"
            orient="auto-start-reverse"><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
        >
        <marker
            id="arwG"
            viewBox="0 0 10 10"
            refX="8.5"
            refY="5"
            markerWidth="7"
            markerHeight="7"
            orient="auto-start-reverse"><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
        >
        <marker
            id="arwR"
            viewBox="0 0 10 10"
            refX="8.5"
            refY="5"
            markerWidth="7"
            markerHeight="7"
            orient="auto-start-reverse"><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9a2417"></path></marker
        >
        <marker
            id="arwM"
            viewBox="0 0 10 10"
            refX="8.5"
            refY="5"
            markerWidth="7"
            markerHeight="7"
            orient="auto-start-reverse"><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#3d54c9"></path></marker
        >
    </defs></svg
>

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 300"
        role="img"
        aria-label="The evaluation loop: collect cases, score them, diff against baseline, ship or roll back, and feed failures back into the golden set. Offline gates pre-ship, online measures post-ship."
    >
        <!-- the loop spine -->
        <rect
            x="26"
            y="120"
            width="104"
            height="46"
            rx="8"
            fill="#eef0fb"
            stroke="#3d54c9"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="78" y="140" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#3d54c9"
            >1 · Collect</text
        >
        <text x="78" y="155" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">golden cases</text>
        <rect
            x="160"
            y="120"
            width="104"
            height="46"
            rx="8"
            fill="#eef0fb"
            stroke="#3d54c9"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="212" y="140" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#3d54c9"
            >2 · Score</text
        >
        <text x="212" y="155" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >prog / human / judge</text
        >
        <rect
            x="294"
            y="120"
            width="104"
            height="46"
            rx="8"
            fill="#eef0fb"
            stroke="#3d54c9"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="346" y="140" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#3d54c9"
            >3 · Diff</text
        >
        <text x="346" y="155" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">vs baseline</text>
        <rect
            x="428"
            y="120"
            width="104"
            height="46"
            rx="8"
            fill="#eef0fb"
            stroke="#3d54c9"
            stroke-width="2"></rect>
        <text x="480" y="140" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#3d54c9"
            >4 · Ship / roll back</text
        >
        <text x="480" y="155" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >decide on the number</text
        >
        <line x1="130" y1="143" x2="156" y2="143" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="264" y1="143" x2="290" y2="143" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <line x1="398" y1="143" x2="424" y2="143" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>

        <!-- feedback arc 5 -->
        <path
            d="M480,166 C480,214 78,214 78,168"
            fill="none"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-width="1.5"
            stroke-dasharray="4 3"
            marker-end="url(#arwG)"></path>
        <text x="279" y="208" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >5 · Feed failures back into the golden set &mdash; the loop closes</text
        >

        <!-- offline vs online bands -->
        <rect
            x="26"
            y="40"
            width="372"
            height="58"
            rx="10"
            fill="#eef0fb"
            stroke="#3d54c9"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="212" y="60" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#3d54c9"
            >OFFLINE &mdash; before you ship</text
        >
        <text x="212" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >fixed dataset · repeatable · runs in CI · gates the merge</text
        >
        <text x="212" y="91" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >same inputs every run</text
        >
        <rect
            x="428"
            y="40"
            width="186"
            height="58"
            rx="10"
            fill="#e9f3ec"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="521" y="60" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >ONLINE &mdash; after you ship</text
        >
        <text x="521" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >live traffic · A/B + shadow</text
        >
        <text x="521" y="91" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >real distribution</text
        >

        <line
            x1="212"
            y1="98"
            x2="280"
            y2="118"
            stroke="#3d54c9"
            stroke-dasharray="3 3"
            marker-end="url(#arwM)"></line>
        <line
            x1="521"
            y1="98"
            x2="490"
            y2="118"
            stroke="#2f5d3a"
            stroke-dasharray="3 3"
            marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>

        <text x="320" y="244" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-style="italic" fill="#3d54c9"
            >The model is a commodity. The dataset of what 'good' means for your task is the moat.</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="266" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >Offline tells you it's safe to ship. Online tells you it actually worked.</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="290" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >You cannot improve what you cannot measure.</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The eval loop in one frame. <b>Collect</b> cases, <b>score</b> them, <b>diff</b> against a baseline,
        <b>ship or roll back</b>, and <b>feed failures back</b>. Offline runs the loop on a fixed
        dataset before ship; online runs it on live traffic after.<sup
            ><a href="#s1" id="r1b">1</a></sup
        >
    </figcaption>
</figure>
